@mboehm7
Please note that re-introduction of guava classes in the project such as in HopDagValidator and RewriteElementwiseMultChainOptimization means that the guava dependency needs to be handled in situations such as scoring using JMLC. The guava-11.0.2 jar is 1.6M, so this can potentially impact the memory footprint required to do JMLC.

cc @bertholdreinwald @frreiss
